Tuesday, May 16, 2017 
#GOD #PROVIDES ALL MY NEEDS 
It is a #Universal #Truth that God, the #Source of ALL life, always provides our needs. It is #impossible for God to withhold from Its #creation. As the #Tree of Life, the #roots are God, and we are the branches. Each branch and all leaves are nourished by the same root system that #nourishes the tree. When there appears to be lack, know that it is just that, an “appearance.” Trust the true Source of your supply and act accordingly. 
I walk by #faith, not by sight. I am not fazed by what my physical eyes are detecting. When I find myself yielding to the #temptation of lack and limitation, I allow the Grace of Love to nudge me back home to the place of peace. I am open and #receptive to all my good, even in this moment. Thank you, Power, in me, through me, as me, around me, through the Christ within. And so it is. 
For we walk by faith, and not by sight. 2 Corinthians 5:7

On my run today my throat was super dry and I didn't have any water on me.  I thought dang, I don't know where I'm going to get water from.  I told myself I trusted God would provide what I need and that he already had.  I also thought maybe someone will actually ask me if I need water.  I got directions from two people and eventually I found ice cold water and cups, how perfect.  I finished my run and I was thinking over things I thought dang, no one offered me any water.  There was a guy parked by where I typically finished with his pups, and long and behold he offers me a bottled water at room temperature. Lol I was blown away and I met a new person who saw me for me.
